        "## `pandas.DataFrame(data,columns)`\n",
        "\n",
        "A `pandas.DataFrame` represents a two dimensional, size-mutable, potentially heterogenous collection of data.\n",
        "\n",
        "`data` can be any iterable, `dict` or another dataframe."
      ],
      "id": "5eaa7848"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "from datetime import date\n",
        "data = {\n",
        "    'Date' : [ date(2025,1,31), date(2025,2,1)],\n",
        "    'Close price' : [ 101.25, 103.00 ]\n",
        "}\n",
        "\n",
        "df = pd.DataFrame(data)\n",
        "df"
      ],
      "id": "5df84b44",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
